This paper discusses the addition of device-to-device (D2D) communication to LTE, which is a topic related to networking and communication (cs.NI). It also involves the optimization of spectrum utilization and overall throughput, which can be considered as information theory (cs.IT) topics. The paper also mentions the potential for new applications and services, such as location-based services (cs.MM). Additionally, the introduction of D2D poses risks to the cellular architecture, which can be seen as a topic related to computer security and cryptography (cs.CR) and system and control theory (cs.SY).
